  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Modeling work items a bit ahead&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Different work items have different levels of complexity and difficulty. Some work items will require more thinking&#xD;
    than others, and the time alloted&amp;nbsp;at the beginning of the iteration for iteration planning may not be enough to&#xD;
    fully understand&amp;nbsp;a given&amp;nbsp;work item. Do not wait until the iteration starts to pull the top work items from&#xD;
    the stack and start working on them.&amp;nbsp;Look a the work items one or two iterations ahead and do&#xD;
    high-level&amp;nbsp;modeling to understand the&amp;nbsp;work items&amp;nbsp;complexity and propose&amp;nbsp;candidate solution to&#xD;
    address the riskiest work items, which helps&amp;nbsp;reduce the overall project risk.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
